  "text": "This embedding takes the direction closest to the one indicated by the Jacobian as most impactful on the model's prediction. By iteratively applying this heuristic to a word sequence, one eventually finds an adversarial input sequence misclassified by the model. The differences between [CITATION_1] and our paper are as follows: 1) We present a black-box attack, in which the adversary doesn't need prior knowledge about the malware classifier, which makes our attack more feasible. 2) We don't modify existing API calls, because while such an attack is relevant for reviews -it might damage a malware functionality which we wish to avoid.",
